    </td>
    <td style="padding-left:20px;">
     The Economic Science Laboratory is located on the ground floor of McClelland Hall.
     <br>
      The lab hosts a diverse group of researchers who are interested in experimentally exploring how people make economic and social decisions.
      <br>
       <br>
        You have the opportunity to earn money from participating in these researchers' experiments.
        <br>
         <br>
          In a typical experiment, you and other participants interact in a strategic game with each other via computers.  Your earnings are based on the decisions that you and the other participants make in the game.  In addition, you are guaranteed to make a certain amount from showing up on time.  You are typically paid in cash at the end of each experiment. Experiments generally last between 30 and 90 minutes.
          <br>
           <br>
            After you register, our researchers will send you invitations to schedule experiments. Details about each experiment — what you have to do, how you will be paid based on your decisions, and so on — are given out by the researchers at the start of each experimental session.
            <br>
             <br/>
             All participation is voluntary and the risks are minimal.
             <br/>
             The University of Arizona's Institutional Review Board has approved the experiments and their methodology.
             <br/>
             <br/>
             Sometimes our researchers will request personal information for financial and tax purposes.  Unless otherwise mentioned, this information will NOT be used for research purposes and CANNOT be linked to the decisions that you made during the experiment.  Every effort will be made to maintain the confidentiality of your personal information.
             <br/>
            </br>
           </br>
          </br>
         </br>
        </br>
       </br>
      </br>
     </br>
    </td>
