  <div class="leightbox" id="privpol">
   <h2>
    Privacy Policy
   </h2>
   We respect your privacy and we take every effort to maintain it.
   <br>
    <br>
     We often collect two different kinds of data from you: personal data and experimental data.
     <br/>
     •   Personal data incudes your name, age, sex, address, phone number, email, and social security number.
     <br/>
     •   Experimental data includes the decisions that you made during the experiment and your outcome in the experiment.
     <br/>
     Personal data is collected for administrative and tax reasons. Experimental data is collected for research purposes.  Both types of data will be stored indefinitely in a secure location on campus.
     <br/>
     <br/>
     Unless you consent, these two kinds of data are kept separate.  This means that your personal data
     <b>
      cannot
     </b>
     be linked to the decisions that you've made during the experiment.
     <br/>
     <br/>
     Sometimes a researcher may ask you to allow some of your personal information to be linked to your experimental information.  For instance, a researcher may ask you whether your age and sex may be linked to your experimental information. It is your choice as to whether or not to allow this information to be linked to your experimental information.  If you refuse, you retain all the money that you have earned up to that point in the experiment.
     <br/>
     <br/>
     We will
     <b>
      never
     </b>
     sell your e-mail address, phone number, or other personal information.  We will
     <b>
      never
     </b>
     make your personal data available to the public.
     <br/>
     <br/>
     We
     <b>
      will
     </b>
     also use your email address to inform you of new opportunities to participate in experiments.  You may opt out of receiving e-mail from us by updating the settings in your account profile.
     <br/>
     <br/>
     We
     <b>
      will
     </b>
     use your personal information for tax and administrative purposes.  We will also use your experimental information for research purposes.  Additionally, regulatory agencies or other oversight bodies may review your experimental information. Since experiments often occur with groups, other people may know that you've participated.
     <br/>
     <br/>
     We may occasionally update our Privacy Policy to reflect changes in our practices. If we make material changes in the way we collect, use, or share your personal information, we will notify you and/or prominently post notices of the changes on our website.
     <br/>
     <br/>
     By participating in experiments at the Economic Sciences Laboratory, you warrant that you have read this policy and consent to it.
     <br/>
